'''Kotai Jinja''' (皇大神社) is a Shinto shrine located in Heimamatsuchō, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県}}{{ill|Nara City|ja|奈良市}}.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|lqt=Great Sun Spirit|lt_ja=大日霊貴命}}
* {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|ja|天児屋命|1=Ame-no-Koyane|lt=Ame-no-Koyane|lt_ja=天児屋根命}}
* {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|1=Iwanaga-hime|lt=Iwanagahime|lt_ja=磐長媛命}}

== Shrine Grounds ==
=== Main Hall ===
Constructed in the Sankan-sha style with a copper-plated roof{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}. It is said to be a relocation of the former main hall of the sessha Mizutani Shrine of {{ill|Kasuga Taisha|ja|春日大社}}, bestowed upon Heimamatsu Sōdai Morita Heitarō—who served as the shrine woodmaster of Kasuga Taisha—due to that connection{{sfn|奈良県史 建築|p=911}}{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Sub-shrines ===
* Itsukushima Shrine – {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|イチキシマヒメ|1=Ichikishima-hime|lt=Ichikishima-hime|lt=Ichikishima-hime|lt_ja=市杵島姫命}}
* Sumiyoshi Shrine – {{ill|Sumiyoshi Sanjin|ja|住吉三神}} {{ill|Kamitsutsunoo|ja|上筒男命}} et al.
They are enshrined on either side of the main hall, each housed in a small shrine with a vermilion-painted Kasuga-style cypress bark roof{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Suinin Emperor's Mausoleum Secondary Mound Remains ===
Within the shrine forest stands a massive andesite boulder {{ill|Andesite|ja|安山岩}}, which is reputed to be the remnant of the secondary mound of the {{ill|Horaiyama Kofun|ja|宝来山古墳|1=Hōraiyama Kofun|lt=Suinin Emperor's Mausoleum|lt_ja=垂仁天皇陵}}{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}. A shimenawa (sacred rope) is strung during the New Year{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Kannon Hall ===
To the west of the shrine grounds stands an area known as Kannon Hall, where old roof tiles and other relics have been discovered{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

== Shrine Treasures ==
=== Kagura Bells ===
An incised inscription reading “{{ill|Keicho|ja|慶長}} 10th year ({{ill|1605|ja|1605th year}}) {{ill|March 16 (Old Calendar)|ja|3月16日 (旧暦)|lt=March Sixteen|lt_ja=三月十六日}} Hiramatsu Uemon” is present{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

