Within the shrine forest stands a massive andesite boulder {{ill|Andesite|ja|安山岩|qq=draft}}, which is reputed to be the remnant of the secondary mound of the {{ill|Horaiyama Kofun|ja|宝来山古墳|1=Hōraiyama Kofun|lt=Suinin Emperor's Mausoleum|lt_ja=垂仁天皇陵|qq=draft}}{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}. A shimenawa (sacred rope) is strung during the New Year{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Kannon Hall ===
To the west of the shrine grounds stands an area known as Kannon Hall, where old roof tiles and other relics have been discovered{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

== Shrine Treasures ==
=== Kagura Bells ===
An incised inscription reading “{{ill|Keicho|ja|慶長|qq=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|1605|ja|1605th year|qq=draft}}) {{ill|March 16 (Old Calendar)|ja|3月16日 (旧暦)|lt=March Sixteen|lt_ja=三月十六日|qq=draft}} Hiramatsu Uemon” is present{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

