=== Kannon Hall ===
To the west of the shrine grounds stands an area known as Kannon Hall, where old roof tiles and other relics have been discovered{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

== Shrine Treasures ==
=== Kagura Bells ===
An incised inscription reading “{{ill|Keicho|ja|慶長|qq=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|1605|ja|1605th year|qq=draft}}) {{ill|March 16 (Old Calendar)|ja|3月16日 (旧暦)|lt=March Sixteen|lt_ja=三月十六日|qq=draft}} Hiramatsu Uemon” is present{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

