'''Kotai Jinja''' (皇大神社) is a Shinto shrine located in Heimamatsuchō, [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]][[:en:Nara (city)|Nara City]].

== Deities ==
* [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]]
* [[:en:Ame-no-Koyane|Ame-no-Koyane]]
* [[:en:Iwanaga-hime|Iwanagahime]]

== Shrine Grounds ==
=== Main Hall ===
Constructed in the Sankan-sha style with a copper-plated roof{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}. It is said to be a relocation of the former main hall of the sessha Mizutani Shrine of [[:en:Kasuga-taisha|Kasuga Taisha]], bestowed upon Heimamatsu Sōdai Morita Heitarō—who served as the shrine woodmaster of Kasuga Taisha—due to that connection{{sfn|奈良県史 建築|p=911}}{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Sub-shrines ===
* Itsukushima Shrine – {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|イチキシマヒメ|1=Ichikishima-hime|lt=Ichikishima-hime|lt=Ichikishima-hime|lt_ja=市杵島姫命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime|qq=}}
* Sumiyoshi Shrine – [[:en:Sumiyoshi sanjin|Sumiyoshi Sanjin]] {{ill|Kamitsutsunoo|ja|上筒男命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsutsunoo|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} et al.
They are enshrined on either side of the main hall, each housed in a small shrine with a vermilion-painted Kasuga-style cypress bark roof{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Suinin Emperor's Mausoleum Secondary Mound Remains ===
Within the shrine forest stands a massive andesite boulder [[:en:Andesite|Andesite]], which is reputed to be the remnant of the secondary mound of the {{ill|Horaiyama Kofun|ja|宝来山古墳|1=Hōraiyama Kofun|lt=Suinin Emperor's Mausoleum|lt_ja=垂仁天皇陵|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horaiyama Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōraiyama Kofun|qq=}}{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}. A shimenawa (sacred rope) is strung during the New Year{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

=== Kannon Hall ===
To the west of the shrine grounds stands an area known as Kannon Hall, where old roof tiles and other relics have been discovered{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

== Shrine Treasures ==
=== Kagura Bells ===
An incised inscription reading “[[:en:Keichō|Keicho]] 10th year ([[:en:1605|1605]]) {{ill|March 16 (Old Calendar)|ja|3月16日 (旧暦)|lt=March Sixteen|lt_ja=三月十六日|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 16 (Old Calendar)|qq=|1=16th day of the 3rd month in the Chinese calendar|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q839338}} Hiramatsu Uemon” is present{{sfn|奈良市史|p=412}}.

